race.comment: SALTY PEARL (1) looks the one to beat coming through the right races for this. She was edged out by subsequent Thousand Guineas winner Ole Dancer two back and got going late for fourth in the Guineas itself, beaten under three lengths. This is easier and she draws well, there just needs to be a bit left in the tank on the backup. RUSKA ROMA (5) was okay in the G2 Edward Manifold at Flemington last time out when battling away for fifth. If she gets a faster tempo to run at here she can certainly win. ENVIABLE (3) comes down from Sydney having worked home fairly in the G1 Flight Stakes for fourth. We've seen that form to be effectively equal to the Melbourne form in the Thousand Guineas. If J-Mac is positive from the wide gate, which isn't a guarantee, she'll take beating. SUNLIT SERENADE (6) has upside and can continue to progress while PRESTIGE SNITZEL (2) is suited up in trip now.
